15:35.560 --> 15:40.300
It's nice to be able to talk to the people who might marvel at what they write, and I reread the stuff.

15:41.340 --> 15:46.940
I don't know how many times I've reread it now, but I wanted to reread it this week, and it's been great.

15:46.940 --> 15:51.460
And from a fan, please hurry up and write another one.

15:51.760 --> 15:54.540
That's exactly the encouragement I need.

15:54.980 --> 15:57.180
I think you might like the new one.

15:57.320 --> 15:58.260
Can I tell you what it's about?

15:58.340 --> 15:59.500
Yeah, I'll go right ahead.

15:59.780 --> 16:11.540
Okay, well, the idea is based upon what happens if for some one reason or another, the very finest portion of humanity simply leaves the planet.

16:13.120 --> 16:22.180
For one reason, I don't know exactly why they get fed up with things, but the very best of the doctors, scientists, God, I guess even the best lawyers can find them.

16:23.640 --> 16:27.640
For over a period of a few years, they just begin leaving and they're gone.

16:28.020 --> 16:30.620
And then afterwards, people realize that A, they are gone.

16:31.520 --> 16:41.500
B, that by leaving, it's the best of left, and what does that mean?

16:41.500 --> 16:42.740
It's very fine folks.

16:44.960 --> 16:56.540
And things after that for either because they left or because people think this is the result of their leaving, it just gets progressively worse and worse and worse.

16:57.280 --> 17:06.120
And after a period of about 40 or 50 years, however, they gradually stabilize after a lot of the usual chaos in this book.

17:06.960 --> 17:12.160
And that's why the heroes, the Attorney General of what's left of the United States, they only go to Chicago.

17:12.980 --> 17:16.740
I'm also having enough guts to actually put the story in real world parts.

17:19.040 --> 17:28.120
And a lot of the action resolves, not the gift of leaving, but the things finally beginning to calm down when it suddenly turns out that they're coming back.

17:32.060 --> 17:32.540
Okay.

17:33.480 --> 17:35.840
Are you think you'll submit it to Dawn?

17:36.660 --> 17:38.300
Well, I was real fortunate.

17:38.480 --> 17:49.500
One of those little stories that when I was a Kenyan, again, I was not in the English section because an English major, because I really thought they were much too intelligent, good for me.

17:50.940 --> 17:56.980
